•
Operational Experience: Provide a plan for achieving operational experience and maturity comparable to established platforms, including incident response playbooks and continuous improvement processes.



5.2. Realistic Adoption Roadmap for DPoP

•
Mandate: Provide a realistic adoption roadmap for DPoP (OAuth 2.0 Demonstrating Proof-of-Possession at the Application Layer), addressing client-side readiness and potential adoption barriers. This must include:

•
Phased Rollout: A phased rollout plan for DPoP, starting with internal applications and gradually expanding to external clients.

•
Client-Side Readiness: Assessment of client-side readiness for DPoP implementation, including browser support, SDK availability, and developer education.

•
Adoption Barriers: Identification of potential adoption barriers (e.g., complexity, lack of tooling) and strategies to overcome them.



5.3. "API Network" and "Security Governance" Elaboration

•
Mandate: Elaborate on the enforcement mechanisms for "Security Governance" and architectural details for the "API Network." This must include:

•
Security Governance Enforcement: The specific tools, processes, and automated checks used to enforce security governance policies across the API lifecycle.

•
API Network Architecture: A detailed architectural design for the "API Network," illustrating how APIs are interconnected, discovered, and secured across the enterprise.



